PeakGuideR included data notice

PeakGuideR includes optional compound and standard-adduct databases for
non-commercial research use.

The compound_mass_database_noncommercial dataset contains records derived from
ChEBI, NORMAN/SusDat and HMDB.

ChEBI-derived records are made available under CC BY 4.0 terms.

NORMAN/SusDat-derived records are made available under CC BY 4.0 terms.

HMDB-derived records are subject to the original HMDB licensing terms, including
CC BY-NC 4.0 non-commercial use restrictions. Commercial use or redistribution
of HMDB-derived records may require explicit permission from HMDB.

The standards_adduct_library_noncommercial dataset contains experimental
standard-adduct information generated by the package authors, together with
compound metadata that may derive from external databases. Where HMDB-derived
metadata are present, the same non-commercial restrictions apply.

Users are responsible for ensuring that their use of the included databases
complies with the licenses and terms of the original data providers.

The PeakGuideR source code and the included third-party-derived data may be
subject to different licensing terms.
